dashboard.definition:
{
	"title": "load_into_indexes",
	"description": "",
	"inputs": {
		"input_indexes": {
			"type": "input.multiselect",
			"title": "Select indexes to export",
			"dataSources": {
				"primary": "ds_index_list"
			},
			"context": {
				"label": "> primary | seriesByName(\"index\") | renameSeries(\"label\")",
				"value": "> primary | seriesByName(\"index\") | renameSeries(\"value\")"
			},
			"options": {
				"defaultValue": "ingest_eval_examples_1,ingest_eval_examples_2",
				"items": "> frame(label, value) | objects()",
				"prefix": "index IN (",
				"delimiter": ", ",
				"suffix": ")",
				"token": "selected_indexes"
			}
		},
		"input_sample_ratio": {
			"type": "input.text",
			"title": "Set sampling",
			"options": {
				"defaultValue": "1",
				"token": "selected_sample_ratio"
			}
		},
		"input_index_time": {
			"type": "input.timerange",
			"title": "Select indexed time range",
			"options": {
				"defaultValue": "-1yr,+1yr",
				"token": "index_time"
			}
		},
		"input_time": {
			"type": "input.timerange",
			"title": "Select timestamp range",
			"options": {
				"defaultValue": "-1y,+1y",
				"token": "time"
			}
		}
	},
	"defaults": {
		"dataSources": {
			"ds.search": {
				"options": {
					"queryParameters": {}
				}
			},
			"ds.spl2": {
				"options": {
					"queryParameters": {}
				}
			}
		},
		"visualizations": {
			"global": {
				"showProgressBar": true
			}
		}
	},
	"visualizations": {
		"viz_markdown": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "# Problem description\n\nOccasionally you may want to export sample data from a production and import it to another. This is especially true when you wish to develop custom props and transforms for enriching data. \n\n## Existing Solutions\nPrimarily you need access to the orignal log files or be able intercept and fork the incoming stream.\n\n## Proposed Solution\nWe write a search that encodes the basic data, `host`, `_raw`, `sourcetype` and `source` into a CSV which can be exported from any splunk instance via search and create a sourcetype which can break up the CSV and write the values back into the appropiate fields\n\n\n### User steps\n\n1. Run the search to capture the sample of data that you require\n1. Export the table as a CSV and export via download in your browser\n1. Use oneshot to load data into splunk specifying the import sourcetype\n\n    /Applications/Splunk/bin/splunk nom on -auth admin:password /Applications/Splunk/etc/apps/ingest_eval_examples/sample/import_data  -sourcetype import_data \n\n\n### The steps performed to import data\n\n1. Break on the line end ^^^END^^^ \n1. Strip the double quotes with SED_CMD, this undoes the splunk encoding of quotes\n1. Read the epoch time stamp from the start of the file\n1. Use a REGEX transform to extract the components for `index`, `host`, `source` and `sourcetype`, write to temporay indexed fields\n1. Use INGEST_EVAL to copy the temporay indexed fields to the correct metadata files\n1. Use INGEST_EVAL and replace to strip the \"header\" from the _raw field\n\n### The search to export data follows:\nThis search finds all data recieved in a one hour period, sampled at one event in every ten and writes the result to a table\n\n    index IN (ingest_eval_examples_1, ingest_eval_examples_2) _index_earliest=-15m _index_latest=now earliest=-1y latest=+1y\n    | noop sample_ratio=10 \n    | eval _raw=_time.\"%%%\".index.\"%%%\".host.\"%%%\".sourcetype.\"%%%\".sourcetype.\"%%%\"._raw.\"^^^END^^^\"\n    | table _raw\n"
			}
		},
		"viz_table": {
			"type": "splunk.table",
			"dataSources": {
				"primary": "ds_export"
			},
			"options": {
				"drilldown": "none"
			},
			"showProgressBar": true,
			"title": "Export rows"
		},
		"viz_conf_props": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "### props.conf\n\nFrom `default/props.conf` \u2014 verbatim:\n\n```ini\n[load_into_indexes]\n# time is stored in epoch at the start of each line\nTIME_FORMAT = %s.%3Q\nTIME_PREFIX = ^\n# the transform required to drop the header extract the metafields and copy to the correct fields\nTRANSFORMS-extract-metadata = load_into_indexes-drop_header, load_into_indexes-extract_metadata_copy_to_meta, load_into_indexes-reassign_meta_to_metadata, load_into_indexes-remove_metadata_from_raw\n# Splunk uses double quotes to escape quotes, we want to remove this before we start extracting the fields\nSEDCMD-strip_double_quotes= s/\"\"/\"/g\n# The solution supports multiline events\nLINE_BREAKER=(\\^\\^\\^END\\^\\^\\^\"\\n)\nSHOULD_LINEMERGE=false\n```\n"
			}
		},
		"viz_conf_transforms": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "### transforms.conf\n\nFrom `default/transforms.conf` \u2014 verbatim:\n\n```ini\n[load_into_indexes-drop_header]\nINGEST_EVAL = queue=if(_raw=\"\\\"_raw\\\"\",\"nullQueue\", queue)\n\n[load_into_indexes-extract_metadata_copy_to_meta]\nSOURCE_KEY=_raw\nWRITE_META = true\nREGEX = ^\"\\d+(?:\\.\\d+)?%%%([^%]+)%%%([^%]+)%%%([^%]+)%%%([^%]+)%%%\nFORMAT = my_index::\"$1\" my_host::\"$2\" my_source::\"$3\" my_sourcetype::\"$4\"\n\n[load_into_indexes-reassign_meta_to_metadata]\nINGEST_EVAL = host:=my_host, source:=my_source, index:=my_index, sourcetype:=my_sourcetype, my_host:=null(), my_source:=null(), my_index:=null(), my_sourcetype:=null()\n\n[load_into_indexes-remove_metadata_from_raw]\nINGEST_EVAL = _raw=replace(_raw, \"^[^%]+%%%(?:[^%]+)%%%(?:[^%]+)%%%(?:[^%]+)%%%(?:[^%]+)%%%(.*)\",\"\\1\")\n```\n"
			}
		}
	},
	"dataSources": {
		"ds_index_list": {
			"name": "Available indexes",
			"type": "ds.search",
			"options": {
				"query": "| eventcount summarize=false index=* index=_* \n| stats sum(count) as count by index \n| sort - count\n| eval label=index.\" (\".count.\")\"",
				"queryParameters": {
					"earliest": "-24h@h",
					"latest": "now"
				}
			}
		},
		"ds_export": {
			"name": "Export search",
			"type": "ds.search",
			"options": {
				"query": "$selected_indexes$ _index_earliest=$index_time.earliest$ _index_latest=$index_time.latest$ earliest=$time.earliest$ latest=$time.latest$\n| noop sample_ratio=$selected_sample_ratio$ \n| eval _raw=_time.\"%%%\".index.\"%%%\".host.\"%%%\".sourcetype.\"%%%\".sourcetype.\"%%%\"._raw.\"^^^END^^^\"\n| table _raw",
				"queryParameters": {
					"earliest": "-24h@h",
					"latest": "now"
				}
			}
		}
	},
	"layout": {
		"globalInputs": [
			"input_indexes",
			"input_sample_ratio",
			"input_index_time",
			"input_time"
		],
		"layoutDefinitions": {
			"layout_1": {
				"type": "grid",
				"options": {
					"width": 1440,
					"height": 250
				},
				"structure": [
					{
						"item": "viz_markdown",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 0,
							"y": 0,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 900
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_table",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 720,
							"y": 0,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 900
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_conf_props",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 0,
							"y": 900,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 480
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_conf_transforms",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 720,
							"y": 900,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 480
						}
					}
				]
			}
		},
		"options": {
			"submitButton": false
		},
		"tabs": {
			"items": [
				{
					"label": "New tab",
					"layoutId": "layout_1"
				}
			]
		}
	},
	"applicationProperties": {
		"hideEdit": false,
		"hideExport": false
	}
}
